e. vasis Corinthiis et Deliacis, ‘ vessels of Corinthian and Delian bronze.’ Cp. Verr. ii. IV, ἐξ 1, 50, 51. Pliny the Elder complains of the decay of metallic art in his own time. See N. H. f. authepsa, αὗθέψης (αὐτός, ἕψω), an automatic boiler.

g. enumeraret. With this reading we may suppose that the sum had been paid down, and that the auctioneer was counting it out, to see if it were right. The other reading ‘ enuntiaret ’ would refer simply to the ‘ praeco ’ crying out the price.
